## **Use Case 1: Automating Sales Trend Analysis with ChatGPT** {#use-case-1:-automating-sales-trend-analysis-with-chatgpt}

Imagine you‚Äôre handed a spreadsheet with quarterly sales data across multiple regions. The task: Spot trends, visualize performance, and summarize key insights for a meeting that starts in 20 minutes.

In the past, this meant pivot tables, charts, and frantic formatting. Today, it means uploading the file to ChatGPT and letting AI do the heavy lifting.

### 

### **Scenario Setup** {#scenario-setup}

**Dataset**: Quarterly sales by region  
**Goal**: Identify growth trends, generate a chart, and summarize performance  
**Tool**: ChatGPT with Advanced Data Analysis

### **Step-by-Step Guide** {#step-by-step-guide}

#### **Step 1: Prepare Your Data** {#step-1:-prepare-your-data}

Create a spreadsheet   
Save it as .csv or .xlsx.

#### **Step 2: Upload to ChatGPT** {#step-2:-upload-to-chatgpt}

* Go to [chat.openai.com](https://chat.openai.com/)  
* Make sure GPT-4 with Advanced Data Analysis is enabled  
* Click the üìé icon to upload your file

#### 

#### **Step 3: Ask Your Prompt** {#step-3:-ask-your-prompt}

Type something like:  
‚ÄúAnalyze this data and show which region had the highest growth. Create a chart and write a summary.‚Äù

ChatGPT will:  
Calculate growth rates ‚Üí Identify top-performing regions ‚Üí Generate a line or bar chart ‚Üí Write a plain-English summary

#### **Step 4: Review the Output** {#step-4:-review-the-output}

A chart showing regional performance over time  
A summary like:  
‚Äú*The North region showed the highest growth at 25%, followed by South (22.2%), East (20%), and West (33.3%). North maintained the highest absolute sales figures throughout the year.*‚Äù

### **Outcome** {#outcome}

In under 5 minutes, you‚Äôve automated:  
A trend analysis, generated a clean visualization, and wrote a meeting-ready summary.

No formulas. No formatting. Just insight.

## **Use Case 2: Customer Segmentation with Notion AI** {#use-case-2:-customer-segmentation-with-notion-ai}

Customer segmentation used to require hours of spreadsheet wrangling, manual tagging, and endless filtering. But with AI tools like Notion AI, you can now generate meaningful customer profiles, behavioral clusters, and actionable insights in minutes‚Äîwithout writing a single line of code.

This chapter walks you through how to use Notion AI to analyze customer feedback, identify segments, and build personas that actually drive decisions.

### **Scenario Setup** {#scenario-setup-1}

**Dataset**: Raw customer feedback and purchase behavior  
**Goal**: Identify customer segments and generate personas  
**Tool**: Notion AI

### **Step-by-Step Guide** {#step-by-step-guide-1}

#### **Step 1: Gather Your Data** {#step-1:-gather-your-data}

Start with a simple table or list in Notion. Example:

Customer Feedback:  
\- ‚ÄúI love the eco-friendly packaging and fast delivery.‚Äù  
\- ‚ÄúThe product quality is great, but I wish there were more color options.‚Äù  
\- ‚ÄúI‚Äôm a repeat buyer‚Äîplease offer loyalty discounts.‚Äù  
\- ‚ÄúShipping took too long. I won‚Äôt order again.‚Äù  
\- ‚ÄúI like the minimalist design and easy checkout process.‚Äù

You can also include purchase history, location, or frequency if available.

#### **Step 2: Ask Notion AI to Summarize** {#step-2:-ask-notion-ai-to-summarize}

Highlight the feedback block and prompt:  
‚ÄúSummarize the key themes and group customers by behavior or preference.‚Äù  
Notion AI will:

* Identify recurring themes (e.g., eco-conscious, design-focused, price-sensitive)  
* Suggest clusters like ‚ÄúLoyal Buyers,‚Äù ‚ÄúStyle Seekers,‚Äù ‚ÄúFrustrated Shoppers‚Äù

#### **Step 3: Generate Personas** {#step-3:-generate-personas}

Prompt:  
‚ÄúCreate customer personas based on these segments. Include name, traits, and buying motivation.‚Äù

Example output:

* **Eco Emma**: Values sustainability and fast shipping. Likely to promote a brand via word-of-mouth.  
* **Design Dave**: Prioritizes aesthetics and ease of use. Responds well to curated product drops.  
* **Loyal Lucy**: Repeat buyer who wants recognition and perks. Ideal for loyalty programs.  
* **Frustrated Frank**: Had a poor experience. Needs re-engagement or win-back strategy.

#### 

#### **Step 4: Turn Insights into Action** {#step-4:-turn-insights-into-action}

Ask Notion AI:  
‚ÄúSuggest marketing strategies for each persona.‚Äù

You‚Äôll get ideas like:

* Eco Emma ‚Üí Highlight green initiatives in email campaigns  
* Loyal Lucy ‚Üí Offer exclusive discounts and early access  
* Frustrated Frank ‚Üí Send apology email with incentive to return

### **Outcome** {#outcome-1}

This case have shown how you can

* Segmented your customers  
* Created actionable personas  
* Designed targeted strategies

No surveys. No clustering algorithms. Just smart AI prompts.

## **‚Ä¶**

## **Use Case 3: Forecasting with Google Sheets \+ GPT** {#use-case-3:-forecasting-with-google-sheets-+-gpt}

Forecasting used to be reserved for data scientists with Python scripts and statistical models. But now, with AI-powered formulas inside Google Sheets, anyone can build predictive models, spot trends, and automate insights right from the spreadsheet.

This chapter walks you through how to use GPT-powered add-ons in Google Sheets to forecast future performance based on historical data.

### **Scenario Setup** {#scenario-setup-2}

**Dataset**: Monthly revenue data  
**Goal**: Forecast next 3 months of revenue  
**Tool**: Google Sheets \+ GPT Add-on (e.g., SheetAI, GPT Workspace)

### **Step-by-Step Guide** {#step-by-step-guide-2}

#### **Step 1: Prepare Your Data** {#step-1:-prepare-your-data-1}

Create a simple table in Google Sheets:

| Month | Revenue ($) |
| :---: | :---: |
| Jan | 12,000 |
| Feb | 13,500 |
| Mar | 14,200 |
| Apr | 15,000 |
| May | 15,800 |
| Jun | 16,500 |

#### **Step 2: Install GPT Add-on** {#step-2:-install-gpt-add-on}

* Go to **Extensions \> Add-ons \> Get add-ons**  
* Search for **SheetAI**, **GPT Workspace**, or similar  
* Install and authorize access

#### **Step 3: Use AI Formula to Forecast** {#step-3:-use-ai-formula-to-forecast}

In a new cell, type a formula like:  
\=GPT("Forecast next 3 months based on the revenue trend")

Or use a prompt cell:  
\=GPT(A1:A6, "Predict revenue for July, August, and September")

The AI will:

* Analyze the trend  
* Apply a linear or exponential model  
* Return forecasted values

#### **Step 4: Visualize the Forecast** {#step-4:-visualize-the-forecast}

Use Google Sheets‚Äô built-in chart tools:

* Select your original and forecasted data  
* Insert a line chart  
* Label future months clearly

### 

### **Outcome** {#outcome-2}

* Forecasted future performance  
* Automated trend analysis  
* Created a visual report

No formulas. No regression models. Just smart AI prompts.

**‚Ä¶**

## **Use Case 4: Automating Research with Perplexity AI** {#use-case-4:-automating-research-with-perplexity-ai}

Research is the backbone of strategic decision-making, but it‚Äôs also one of the most time-consuming tasks in analytics. Whether you're exploring market trends, competitor moves, or customer behavior, digging through articles, reports, and data can eat up hours.

Enter **Perplexity AI**, a conversational search engine that doesn‚Äôt just find information, it summarizes it, cites it, and helps you think through it. 

In this chapter, you‚Äôll learn how to use Perplexity to automate research and turn raw information into actionable insights.

### 

### **Scenario Setup** {#scenario-setup-3}

**Goal**: Research emerging trends in online retail  
**Tool**: [Perplexity AI](https://www.perplexity.ai/)  
**Use Case**: Summarize sources, compare competitors, generate strategic recommendations

### **Step-by-Step Guide** {#step-by-step-guide-3}

#### **Step 1: Ask a Strategic Question** {#step-1:-ask-a-strategic-question}

Go to [perplexity.ai](https://www.perplexity.ai/) and type:  
‚ÄúWhat are the top emerging trends in online retail for 2025?‚Äù  
Perplexity will:

* Search across trusted sources  
* Summarize key trends (e.g., AI personalization, live shopping, sustainable logistics)  
* Provide citations so you can verify or dive deeper

#### **Step 2: Refine Your Focus** {#step-2:-refine-your-focus}

Follow up with:  
‚ÄúCompare how Amazon and Shopify are responding to these trends.‚Äù  
You‚Äôll get:

* A side-by-side summary of strategies  
* Insights into product innovation, logistics, and customer experience  
* Links to source articles and reports

#### **Step 3: Generate Strategic Insights** {#step-3:-generate-strategic-insights}

Ask:  
‚ÄúWhat opportunities do these trends create for mid-size fashion retailers?‚Äù  
Perplexity will suggest:

* Personalized shopping experiences using AI  
* Sustainable packaging as a brand differentiator  
* Influencer-led live commerce strategies

#### **Step 4: Turn Research into Action** {#step-4:-turn-research-into-action}

Copy the summary into Notion or Google Docs and prompt ChatGPT:  
‚ÄúTurn this research into a 3-point strategy plan for a fashion retailer.‚Äù

You‚Äôll get a clean, actionable framework ready for presentation or execution.

### **Outcome** {#outcome-3}

* Researched a complex topic  
* Compared competitors  
* Generated strategic recommendations

No endless tabs. No PDF skimming. Just focused, AI-powered insight.  
				**‚Ä¶**

## **Use Case 5: Automating Reporting with Harpa AI** {#use-case-5:-automating-reporting-with-harpa-ai}

Reporting is one of the most repetitive tasks in analytics. You check dashboards, copy numbers, paste them into slides, write summaries and repeat it all next week. But what if an AI agent could do that for you?

**Harpa AI** is a browser-based automation tool that acts like a personal assistant for your data. It can monitor websites, extract metrics, summarize pages, and even trigger alerts or emails‚Äîall without writing code.  
This chapter shows you how to use Harpa AI to automate reporting workflows and free up hours of manual effort.

### **Scenario Setup** {#scenario-setup-4}

**Goal**: Monitor a sales dashboard and generate weekly performance summaries  
**Tool**: [Harpa AI](https://www.harpa.ai/)  
**Use Case**: Automate reporting, extract KPIs, summarize insights

### **Step-by-Step Guide** {#step-by-step-guide-4}

#### **Step 1: Install Harpa AI** {#step-1:-install-harpa-ai}

* Visit [harpa.ai](https://www.harpa.ai/)  
* Install the Chrome extension  
* Pin it to your browser toolbar

#### **Step 2: Open Your Dashboard** {#step-2:-open-your-dashboard}

Navigate to your BI dashboard (e.g., Power BI, Tableau, Google Data Studio). Make sure key metrics like revenue, conversion rate, and top products are visible.

#### **Step 3: Create a Harpa Command** {#step-3:-create-a-harpa-command}

Click the Harpa icon and create a new command:  
‚ÄúSummarize this dashboard. Extract revenue, conversion rate, and top 3 products. Write a weekly performance summary.‚Äù

Harpa will:

* Scan the page  
* Extract visible metrics  
* Generate a summary in natural language

#### **Step 4: Schedule the Report** {#step-4:-schedule-the-report}

Set Harpa to run this command every Friday at 4 PM. You can:

* Save the summary to Notion or Google Docs  
* Email it to your team  
* Trigger a Slack message

**You can also**

* Monitor competitor websites for price changes  
* Track blog traffic or SEO metrics  
* Summarize news articles or press releases

### **Outcome** {#outcome-4}

* Automated your weekly reporting  
* Eliminated manual copy-paste  
* Created a repeatable, scalable workflow

No scripts. No integrations. Just browser-based AI magic.

